### 7. GlowButton - Primary Action Button
```dart
// lib/presentation/widgets/glow_button.dart

class GlowButton extends StatelessWidget {
  final String text;
  final VoidCallback onPressed;
  final Color? color;
  final Color? textColor;
  final IconData? icon;
  final bool isSecondary;
  
  const GlowButton({
    Key? key,
    required this.text,
    required this.onPressed,
    this.color,
    this.textColor,
    this.icon,
    this.isSecondary = false,
  }) : super(key: key);
  
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final buttonColor = color ?? 
        (isSecondary ? AppColors.slate : AppColors.electric);
    final textCol = textColor ?? 
        (isSecondary ? AppColors.mica : Colors.white);
    
    return GestureDetector(
      onTap: onPressed,
      child: AnimatedContainer(
        duration: const Duration(milliseconds: 200),
        padding: const EdgeInsets.symmetric(
          horizontal: 24,
          vertical: 16,
        ),
        decoration: BoxDecoration(
          color: buttonColor,
          borderRadius: AppRadius.button,
          boxShadow: isSecondary 
              ? null 
              : AppShadows.glowElectric,
        ),
        child: Row(
          mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
          children: [
            if (icon != null) ...[
              FaIcon(icon, color: textCol, size: 20),
              const SizedBox(width: 12),
            ],
            Text(
              text.toUpperCase(),
              style: AppTextStyles.h3.copyWith(
                color: textCol,
                fontSize: 18,
              ),
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

## Widget Best Practices

### 1. Extract Sub-Widgets
```dart
// BAD: Everything in build()
@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  return Column(
    children: [
      Container(/* 50 lines of code */),
      Row(/* 30 lines of code */),
      // etc...
    ],
  );
}

// GOOD: Extract to methods or widgets
@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  return Column(
    children: [
      _buildHeader(),
      _buildContent(),
      _buildFooter(),
    ],
  );
}
```

### 2. Use const Constructors
```dart
const SizedBox(height: 16),
const Spacer(),
const Divider(color: AppColors.slate),
```

### 3. Parameterize for Reusability
```dart
class StatDisplay extends StatelessWidget {
  final String label;
  final String value;
  final Color? valueColor;
  
  const StatDisplay({
    required this.label,
    required this.value,
    this.valueColor,
  });
}
```

### 4. Handle Null Safety Properly
```dart
final color = widget.color ?? AppColors.electric;
final text = widget.text?.toUpperCase() ?? '';
```

## Widget Testing Tips

1. Extract widgets to separate files for easier testing
2. Use Keys for finding widgets in tests
3. Keep widgets pure (no side effects in build)
4. Test widget variations with different parameters
